9fb59cebdbcc3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222860%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI%20whistleblowers%20wrote%20to%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission.%3Cp%3ECFOTO%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI%20whistleblowers%20urged%20the%20SEC%20to%20investigate%20the%20ChatGPT%20maker%20for%20potential%20rule%20violations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20whistleblowers%20claim%20OpenAI%20used%20nondisclosure%20agreements%20(NDAs)%20to%20silence%20employees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20letter%20was%20sent%20to%20SEC%20chair%C2%A0Gary%20Gensler%20and%C2%A0Sen.%20Chuck%20Grassley's%20office.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20whistleblowers%20are%20calling%20on%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20to%20investigate%20whether%20the%20ChatGPT%20maker%20violated%20SEC%20rules%20and%20prevented%20employees%20from%20speaking%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELegally%20protected%20whistleblowers%20sent%20a%20letter%20to%20Gary%20Gensler%2C%20chair%20of%20the%20SEC%2C%20on%20July%201%20calling%20on%20the%20regulator%20to%20investigate%20OpenAI.%20The%20letter%2C%20which%20was%20also%20sent%20to%20Sen.%20Chuck%20Grassley's%20office%2C%20was%20later%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20states%20that%20the%20whistleblowers%20provided%20documents%20to%20the%20SEC%20supporting%20their%20claims%20that%20OpenAI's%20NDAs%20%26quot%3Bviolated%20numerous%20precedents%20of%20the%20SEC.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Grassley%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider%20that%20assessing%20the%20threats%20posed%20by%20AI%20fell%20under%20Congress's%20constitutional%20responsibility%20to%20protect%20national%20security.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BOpenAI's%20policies%20and%20practices%20appear%20to%20cast%20a%20chilling%20effect%20on%20whistleblowers'%20right%20to%20speak%20up%20and%20receive%20due%20compensation%20for%20their%20protected%20disclosures.%20In%20order%20for%20the%20federal%20government%20to%20stay%20one%20step%20ahead%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20OpenAI's%20nondisclosure%20agreements%20must%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%20An%20SEC%20representative%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20SEC%20does%20not%20comment%20on%20the%20existence%20or%20nonexistence%20of%20a%20possible%20whistleblower%20submission.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whistleblowers'%20complaint%20comes%20after%20Vox%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2Ffuture-perfect%2F2024%2F5%2F17%2F24158478%2Fopenai-departures-sam-altman-employees-chatgpt-release%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20May%20that%20OpenAI%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaked-docs-openai-pressure-departing-employees-vox-altman-nda-nondisclosure-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecould%20take%20back%20vested%20equity%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20departing%20employees%20if%20they%20did%20not%20sign%20non-disparagement%20agreements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20Altman%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-nda-clause-vested-equity-ilya-sutskever-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esaid%20on%20X%20shortly%20after%20the%20report%20was%20published%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20know%20this%20was%20happening.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENine%20former%20and%20current%20OpenAI%20employees%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-employee-letter-google-deepmind-ai-risks-protections-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esigned%20an%20open%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June%20calling%20on%20major%20AI%20firms%20to%20ensure%20greater%20transparency%20and%20better%20protections%20for%20whistleblowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliam%20Saunders%2C%20a%20former%20OpenAI%20employee%20who%20quit%20earlier%20this%20year%20after%20losing%20confidence%20that%20the%20company%20could%20responsibly%20mitigate%20AI%20risks%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-engineer-quit-safety-concerns-right-warn-letter-sam-altman-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20BI%20about%20what%20led%20to%20him%20signing%20the%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20speaking%20out.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHe%20said%20an%20incident%20in%20which%20another%20former%20OpenAI%20employee%2C%20Leopold%20Aschenbrenner%2C%20was%20fired%20and%20the%20requirement%20that%20OpenAI%20staff%20sign%20NDAs%20led%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-employee-letter-google-deepmind-ai-risks-protections-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efour%20principles%20set%20out%20in%20the%20June%20open%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dde8bdb7-9248-46e5-b28e-39963c9e876d%5C%22%3ERead%20the%20full%20letter%20sent%20to%20the%20SEC%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20Honorable%20Gary%20Gensler%20%3Cbr%3EChair%2C%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%3Cbr%3E100%20FStreet%2C%20NE%20Washington%2C%20DC%2020549%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EJuly%201%2C%202024%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%3Cstrong%3ERe%3A%20OpenAI%20Violations%20of%20Rule%2021F-17(a)%20and%20Implementation%20of%20E.O.%2014110%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EDear%20Chair%20Gensler%3A%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EWe%20represent%20the%20one%20or%20more%20anonymous%20and%20confidential%20whistleblowers)%20who%20filed%20a%20formal%20TCR%20complaint%20with%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20(%26quot%3BSEC%26quot%3B)%20documenting%20systemic%20violations%20of%20the%20Dodd-Frank%20Act%2C%2015%20U.S.C.%20%C2%A7%20784-6%20and%20SEC%20Rule%2021F-17(a)%20committed%20by%20OpenAI.%20OpenAl%20is%20a%20San%20Francisco%20based%20tech%20company%20most%20well-known%20for%20its%20artificial%20intelligence%20(%26quot%3BAI%26quot%3B)%20product%20ChatGPT%3F%20Under%20SEC%20precedent%2C%20and%20as%20a%20mater%20of%20law%2C%20OpenAI%20is%20required%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20SEC's%20regulation%20prohibiting%20illegally%20restrictive%20non-disclosure%20agreements%20(%26quot%3BNDAS%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EAs%20explained%20in%20the%20complaint%2C%20OpenAI's%20employment%2C%20severance%2C%20non-disparagement%2C%20and%20non-%20disclosure%20agreements%20violated%20SEC%20Rule%2021F-17(a).%20The%20agreements%20prohibited%20and%20discouraged%20both%20employees%20and%20investors%20from%20communicating%20with%20the%20SEC%20concerning%20securities%20violations%2C%20forced%20employees%20to%20waive%20their%20rights%20ot%20whistleblower%20incentives%20and%20compensation%2C%20and%20required%20employees%20to%20notify%20the%20company%20of%20communication%20with%20government%20regulators.%20The%20SEC%20has%20made%20it%20abundantly%20clear%20that%20privately%20held%20companies%20that%20engage%20in%20these%20practices%20violate%20the%20law%20and%20are%20subject%20to%20fines%20and%20other%20enforcement%20actions.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EGiven%20the%20risks%20associated%20with%20the%20advancement%20of%20AI%2C%20there%20si%20an%20urgent%20need%20to%20ensure%20that%20employees%20working%20on%20this%20technology%20understand%20that%20they%20can%20raise%20complaints%20or%20address%20concerns%20to%20federal%20regulatory%20or%20law%20enforcement%20authorities.%20Likewise%2C%20it%20is%20critical%20for%20companies%20like%20OpenAI%20to%20understand%20the%20illegal%20nature%20of%20their%20NDAs%2C%20and%20to%20ensure%20that%20their%20workplace%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20SEC%20must%20take%20swift%20and%20aggressive%20steps%20to%20enforce%20SEC%20Rule%2021F-17(a)%20within%20the%20AI%20sector%2C%20and%20to%20ensure%20that%20there%20have%20been%20no%20violations%20of%2018%20U.S.C.%20%C2%A7%201513(e).%20Executive%20Order%2014110%20requires%20nothing%20less%2C%20acknowledging%20that%20every%20agency%20of%20the%20federal%20government%20is%20responsible%20for%20%26quot%3Bmitigating%26quot%3B%20the%20%26quot%3Bsubstantial%20risks%26quot%3B%20posed%20by%20AI.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20Executive%20Order%20warns%20that%20%26quot%3BArtificial%20intelligence%20(AI)%20holds%20extraordinary%20potential%20for%20.%20.%20.%20peril%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Birresponsible%20use%26quot%3B%20of%20this%20emerging%20technology%20%26quot%3Bcould%20exacerbate%20societal%20harms%20such%20as%20fraud%2C%20discrimination%2C%20bias%2C%20and%20disinformation%3B%20displace%20and%20disempower%20workers%3B%20stifle%20competition%3B%20and%20pose%20risks%20to%20national%20security.%26quot%3B%20The%20Executive%20Order%20therefore%20concludes%20that%20ensuring%20the%20safe%20development%20of%20AI%20technology%20%26quot%3Bdemands%20a%20society-wide%20effort%20that%20includes%20government%2C%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20academia%2C%20and%20civil%20society.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ETo%20achieve%20this%20end%2C%20the%20Order%20mandates%20that%20agencies%20such%20as%20the%20SEC%20enforce%20existing%20laws%20designed%20to%20protect%20the%20public%20and%20investors%20from%20fraud.9%20At%20the%20heart%20of%20any%20such%20enforcement%20effort%20is%20the%20recognition%20that%20insiders%20(i.e.%20whistleblowers)%20must%20be%20free%20to%20report%20concerns%20to%20federal%20authorities.%20Moreover%2C%20these%20employees%20need%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20their%20rights%20under%20the%20Dodd-Frank%20Act%20to%20file%20such%20reports%20confidentially%20and%20anonymously%20directly%20with%20the%20SEC.%20They%20also%20need%20to%20know%20that%20they%20cannot%20be%20retaliated%20against%20for%20making%20such%20reports%2C%20and%20that%20they%20are%20potentially%20eligible%20for%20compensation%20if%20their%20reports%20result%20in%20successful%20enforcement%20actions%20designed%20to%20protect%20the%20public%20and%20investors.%20Employees%20are%20in%20the%20best%20position%20to%20detect%20and%20warn%20against%20the%20types%20of%20dangers%20referenced%20in%20the%20Executive%20Order%20and%20are%20also%20in%20the%20best%20position%20to%20help%20ensure%20that%20AI%20benefits%20humanity%2C%20instead%20of%20having%20an%20opposite%20effect.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20SEC's%20Whistleblower%20Office%20was%20provided%20with%20significant%20documentation%20demonstrating%20that%20OpenAI's%20prior%20NDAs%20violated%20the%20law%20by%20requiring%20its%20employees%20to%20sign%20illegally%20restrictive%20contracts%20to%20obtain%20employment%2C%20severance%20payments%2C%20and%20other%20financial%20consideration.%20Given%20the%20well-documented%20potential%20risks%20posed%20by%20the%20irresponsible%20deployment%20of%20AI%2C%20we%20urge%20the%20Commissioners%20to%20immediately%20approve%20an%20investigation%20into%20OpenAI's%20prior%20NDAs%2C%20and%20to%20review%20current%20efforts%20apparently%20being%20undertaken%20by%20the%20company%20to%20ensure%20full%20compliance%20with%20SEC%20Rule%2021F-17(a).%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThis%20request%20for%20an%20investigation%20is%20fully%20supported%20by%20the%20documents%20provided%20to%20the%20SEC%20by%20the%20Whistleblower(s).%20The%20agreements%20attached%20as%20exhibits%20to%20the%20SEC%20complaint%20support%20a%20finding%20that%20OpenAI's%20use%20of%20the%20NDAs%20submitted%20with%20the%20complaint%20violated%20numerous%20precedents%20of%20the%20SEC.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ESEC%20precedent%20requires%20that%20an%20effective%20enforcement%20action%20be%20undertaken%20based%20on%20the%20NDAs%20provided%20as%20evidence%20in%20the%20Dodd-Frank%20complaint.%20In%20the%20SEC's%20first%20case%20addressing%20the%20issue%20of%20improper%20NDAs%2C%20the%20Commission%20sanctioned%20KBR%20for%20an%20NDA%20drafted%20before%20the%20Dodd-Frank%20Act%20was%20even%20passed.%20The%20company%20was%20sanctioned%20despite%20agreeing%20to%20fix%20the%20language%20in%20the%20NDAs%2C%20and%20despite%20the%20agreeing%20to%20contact%20employees%20who%20had%20executed%20these%20agreements%20in%20the%20past%20and%20informing%20them%20directly%20of%20their%20right%20to%20report%20wrongdoing%20to%20the%20appropriate%20authorities.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EAdditionally%2C%20given%20the%20large%20number%20of%20improper%20NDAs%20used%20by%20OpenAI%20over%20a%20long%20period%20of%20time%2C%20it%20is%20imperative%20that%20the%20Commission%20ensure%20that%20all%20prior%20improper%20NDAs%20be%20cured%2C%20and%20that%20any%20corrective%20action%20taken%20by%20OpenAI%20is%20consistent%20with%20past%20Commission%20precedent.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThe%20courage%20of%20our%20client(s)%20in%20coming%20forward%20creates%20an%20opportunity%20to%20help%20ensure%20that%20all%20participants%20in%20creating%20and%20marketing%20this%20new%20technology%20will%20firmly%20understand%20that%20employees%20and%20investors%20always%20have%20the%20right%20to%20report%20wrongdoing%2C%20safety%20issues%2C%20and%20violations%20of%20law%20to%20the%20appropriate%20authorities.%20The%20chilling%20effect%20of%20prior%20NDAs%20and%20the%20harmful%20message%20these%20illegal%20contracts%20create%20within%20the%20workplace%20culture%20needs%20to%20be%20addressed%20in%20an%20appropriate%20enforcement%20action%2C%20designed%20to%20fully%20address%20any%20harmful%20impact%20caused%20by%20these%20practices.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EAccountably%20is%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20deterrence%2C%20and%20deterrence%20is%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20Dodd-Frank%20Act.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EAmong%20the%20violations%20documented%20by%20the%20Whistleblower(s)%20are%3A%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%E2%80%A2%20Non-disparagement%20clauses%20that%20failed%20to%20exempt%20disclosures%20of%20securities%20violations%20to%20the%20SEC%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%E2%80%A2%20Requiring%20prior%20consent%20from%20the%20company%20to%20disclose%20confidential%20information%20to%20federal%20authorities%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%E2%80%A2%20Confidentiality%20requirements%20with%20respect%20to%20agreements%2C%20that%20themselves%20contain%20securities%20violations%3B%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%E2%80%A2%20Requiring%20employees%20to%20waive%20compensation%20that%20was%20intended%20by%20Congress%20to%20incentivize%20reporting%20and%20provide%20financial%20relief%20to%20whistleblowers%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EAs%20we%20expressed%20above%2C%20even%20if%20OpenAI%20is%20making%20reforms%20in%20light%20of%20the%20public%20disclosures%20of%20their%20illegal%20contracts%2C%20the%20importance%20of%20taking%20appropriate%20enforcement%20action%20is%20critical%20%E2%80%93%20not%20as%20an%20attack%20on%20OpenAI%20or%20to%20hinder%20the%20advancement%20of%20AI%20technology%2C%20but%20to%20send%20the%20message%20to%20others%20in%20the%20AI%20space%2C%20and%20to%20the%20tech%20industry%20at%20large%2C%20that%20violations%20on%20the%20right%20of%20employees%20or%20investors%20to%20report%20wrongdoing%20will%20not%20be%20tolerated.%20The%20door%20must%20be%20open%20for%20potential%20whistleblowers%20both%20at%20OpenAI%20and%20at%20other%20companies%20to%20come%20forward%20concerning%20misconduct%20and%20safety%20issues%20possibly%20occurring%20throughout%20the%20field.%20The%20law%20requires%20that%20such%20complaints%20be%20welcomed%20and%20rewarded%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20law%20and%20policy%2C%20not%20discouraged%20by%20companies%20sending%20direct%20or%20indirect%20messages%20to%20employees%20that%20they%20must%20honor%20a%20%26quot%3Bcode%20of%20silence%26quot%3B%20that%20has%20resulted%20in%20so%20many%20disasters%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EAs%20the%20Senate%20Judiciary%20Committee%20pointed%20out%20in%20its%20report%20on%20the%20Sarbanes-Oxley%20Act%2C%20the%20SEC-%20enforced%20whistleblower%20laws%20are%20intended%20to%20specifically%20target%20and%20eliminate%20the%20corporate%20culture%20that%20inhibits%20lawful%20disclosure%20to%20law%20enforcement%20or%20regulatory%20authorities%3A%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E%5BThe%5D%20%26quot%3Bcorporate%20code%20of%20silence%26quot%3B%20not%20only%20hampers%20investigations%2C%20but%20also%20creates%20a%20climate%20where%20ongoing%20wrongdoing%20can%20occur%20with%20virtual%20impunity.%20The%20consequences%20of%20this%20corporate%20code%20of%20silence%20for%20investors%20in%20publicly%20traded%20companies%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20and%20for%20the%20stock%20market%2C%20in%20general%2C%20are%20serious%20and%20adverse%2C%20and%20they%20must%20be%20remedied.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3ESEC%20action%20here%20is%20perhaps%20the%20best%20way%20for%20development%20of%20this%20rapidly%20evolving%20and%20important%20industry%20to%20proceed%20in%20a%20safe%2C%20transparent%20manner.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EGiven%20the%20potential%20that%20advanced%20AI%20could%20%26quot%3Bpose%20an%20existential%20risk%20to%20humanity%2C%26quot%3B%20restrictive%20nondisclosure%20agreements%20are%20particularly%20egregious.%20We%20therefore%20request%20that%20the%20SEC%20take%20the%20following%20actions%20to%20quickly%20and%20effectively%20reinforce%20to%20OpenAI%20and%20all%20of%20their%20employees%20or%20investors%20%E2%80%93%20as%20well%20as%20employees%20of%20other%20companies%20in%20this%20space%20%E2%80%93%20that%20they%20have%20a%20right%20to%20file%20claims%20with%20the%20SEC%20and%20other%20federal%20or%20state%20law%20enforcement%20or%20regulatory%20authorities%3A%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E1.%20Require%20OpenAl%20to%20produce%20for%20inspection%20every%20employment%20agreement%2C%20severance%20agreement%2C%20investor%20agreement%2C%20or%20any%20other%20contract%20that%20contains%20a%20nondisclosure%20agreement.%20Upon%20review%20of%20these%20agreements%2C%20the%20SEC%20can%20ensure%20that%20none%20of%20the%20employees%20or%20other%20persons%20who%20signed%20these%20agreements%20suffered%20any%20harm%20that%20is%20explicitly%20prohibited%20under%20the%20Sarbanes-Oxley%20Act's%20obstruction%20of%20justice%20provision%2C%2018%20U.S.C.%20%C2%A7%201513(e).%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E2.%20Require%20OpenAl%20to%20notify%20al%20past%20and%20current%20employees%20as%20to%20the%20violations%20they%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3Ecommitted%2C%20notify%20every%20past%20and%20current%20employee%20that%20pursuant%20to%20the%20Dodd-Frank%20Act%20employees%20have%20the%20right%20to%20confidentially%20and%20anonymously%20report%20any%20violations%20of%20law%20ot%20the%20SEC%2C%20and%20inform%20them%20of%20all%20the%20rights%20associated%20with%20such%20a%20report.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E3.%20Fine%20OpenAl%20for%20each%20improper%20agreement%20under%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Act%20to%20the%20extent%20the%20SEC%20deems%20appropriate.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3E4.%20Direct%20OpenAI%20to%20cure%20the%20%26quot%3Bchilling%20effect%26quot%3B%20of%20its%20past%20practices%20consistent%20with%20the%20affirmative%20relief%20in%20prior%20Commission%20decisions.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3Csection%3EThank%20you%20for%20your%20time%20and%20consideration.%20We%20remain%20available%20to%20assist%20the%20government%20on%20this%20matter%20in%20any%20way%20going%20forward.%3C%2Fsection%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-letter-openai-whistleblowers-sent-sec-action-nda-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721210138000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66968bf75439fb59cebdc127%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-letter-openai-whistleblowers-sent-sec-action-nda-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22OpenAI%20whistleblowers%20wrote%20to%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20seeking%20an%20investigation%20into%20whether%20the%20ChatGPT%20maker%20violated%20SEC%20rules.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jmann%40insider.com%20(Jyoti%20Mann)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F