nvestor%2C%20the%20kind%20of%20guy%20who%20scours%20the%20internet%20to%20find%20nearby%20rents%20and%20combs%20through%20new%20listings%20with%20an%20eye%20toward%20expanding%20his%20mini%20empire.%20He%20owns%20nearly%2030%20rental%20homes%2C%20and%20while%20he%20outsources%20their%20day-to-day%20management%20to%20a%20large%20company%2C%20he%20makes%20sure%20his%20properties%20are%20within%20a%201%C2%BD%20-hour%20drive%20of%20his%20Atlanta%20home%20so%20he%20can%20stop%20by%20if%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReal-estate%20insiders%20often%20divide%20owners%20of%20single-family%20rental%20homes%20into%20two%20groups.%20There%20are%20the%20big%20guys%20%E2%80%94%20a%20small%20number%20of%20cash-flush%20%26quot%3BWall%20Street%20investors%26quot%3B%20who%20own%20hundreds%20or%20thousands%20of%20properties%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20little%20guys%2C%20or%20mom-and-pops%2C%20who%20own%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20single-family%20rentals.%20The%20stark%2C%20black-and-white%20divide%20has%20proved%20useful%20for%20all%20types%20of%20groups%3A%20Big%20companies%20point%20to%20the%20prevalence%20of%20mom-and-pops%20as%20proof%20that%20corporations%20like%20themselves%20are%20nowhere%20close%20to%20taking%20over%20the%20market.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstop-wall-street-landlords-single-family-rental-homes-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPoliticians%20invoke%20the%20Ms-and-Ps%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20highlight%20the%20contrast%20between%20the%20new%20class%20of%20greedy%20Wall%20Street%20landlords%20and%20the%20industry's%20humble%20origins.%20But%20Daniel%2C%20who%20requested%20anonymity%20to%20speak%20freely%20about%20his%20investments%2C%20is%20a%20prime%20example%20of%20the%20blurring%20line%20between%20the%20two%20factions%20%E2%80%94%20nowhere%20near%20the%20size%20of%20the%20private-equity%20firms%20who%20gobbled%20up%20entire%20blocks%20of%20homes%20during%20the%20pandemic%20but%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20old%20guy%20who%20lives%20downstairs%20and%20hasn't%20raised%20rent%20in%20a%20couple%20of%20years.%20In%20this%20binary%20world%2C%20he's%20stuck%20with%20the%20mom-and-pop%20moniker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20past%20few%20years%20have%20solidified%20single-family%20rental%20homes%20as%20genuine%20moneymaking%20enterprises%2C%20not%20just%20ho-hum%20nest%20eggs.%20It%20costs%20nothing%20for%20small-time%20landlords%20to%20cruise%20through%20Zillow%20and%20see%20what%20their%20neighbors%20are%20charging%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20price%20their%20rentals%20more%20aggressively.%20Meanwhile%2C%20a%20whole%20ecosystem%20of%20startups%20has%20sprung%20up%20to%20meet%20the%20every%20need%20of%20mom-and-pop%20landlords%2C%20from%20basic%20stuff%20like%20tenant%20screening%20to%20the%20minutiae%20of%20air-filter%20delivery.%20Bryan%20Smith%2C%20the%20chief%20operating%20officer%20of%20AMH%20Homes%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20truly%20big%20landlords%2C%20with%20a%20portfolio%20of%20more%20than%2059%2C000%20homes%20%E2%80%94%20noted%20in%20a%20recent%20call%20with%20analysts%20that%20mom-and-pops%20hadn't%20traditionally%20been%20known%20for%20raising%20rents.%20But%20over%20time%2C%20he%20said%2C%20they've%20%26quot%3Bmigrated%20into%20a%20strategy%20that's%20closer%26quot%3B%20to%20that%20of%20big%20players%20such%20as%20AMH.%20Translation%3A%20The%20Wall%20Street%20mindset%20has%20gone%20mainstream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20time%20to%20retire%20the%20label%20of%20%26quot%3Bmom-and-pop%20landlord.%26quot%3B%20There%20may%20be%20plenty%20of%20aging%20couples%20or%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthis-startup-retirement-solution-single-family-rental-landlords-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccidental%20landlords%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20sailing%20into%20retirement%20with%20an%20investment%20home%20or%20two%20in%20their%20back%20pockets%2C%20but%20even%20the%20smallest%20of%20landlords%2C%20lured%20by%20the%20promise%20of%20greater%20efficiency%20and%20fatter%20profits%2C%20may%20no%20longer%20be%20content%20to%20merely%20have%20heads%20in%20beds.%20A%20steady%20stream%20of%20rental%20data%20and%20an%20onslaught%20of%20new%20property-management%20services%20have%20made%20amateur%20landlords%20savvier%20than%20ever.%20And%20that's%20to%20say%20nothing%20of%20the%20changing%20of%20the%20guard%20as%20baby%20boomers%20age%20out%20of%20their%20property-owning%20days%2C%20which%20leaves%20millennials%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-real-estate-investing-mistakes-buying-homes-early-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Zers%20to%20take%20on%20the%20mantle%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20your%20kindly%20mom-and-pop%20landlord%20is%20about%20to%20get%20a%20lot%20more%20cutthroat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20recently%2C%20there%20was%20no%20need%20to%20distinguish%20between%20mom-and-pop%20owners%20of%20single-family%20rentals%20and%20their%20suit-clad%20counterparts.%20Institutional%20landlords%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-family-rental-investor-conference-buying-more-homes-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emassive%20investment%20managers%20with%20billions%20of%20dollars%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20spend%20on%20single-family%20homes%20%E2%80%94%20didn't%20exist%20before%20the%20housing%20market's%20crash%20in%202008.%20Most%20big%20investors%20assumed%20it%20would%20be%20too%20complicated%20and%20expensive%20to%20manage%20portfolios%20of%20homes%20scattered%20across%20neighborhoods%20and%20cities.%20Corporate%20behemoths%20were%20content%20to%20spend%20big%20on%20apartment%20buildings%20and%20let%20the%20little%20guys%20handle%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20burst%20of%20the%20housing%20bubble%20flipped%20this%20logic%20on%20its%20head.%20An%20abundance%20of%20cheap%20homes%20offered%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorporate-landlords-ready-110-billion-to-pounce-on-homes-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperfect%20entry%20point%20for%20private-equity-backed%20firms%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20new%20technology%20allowed%20large%20companies%20to%20efficiently%20and%20cheaply%20manage%20properties%20scattered%20across%20the%20country.%20Between%202007%20and%202014%2C%20the%20number%20of%20single-family%20rentals%20jumped%20from%20fewer%20than%2012%20million%20to%20more%20than%2015%20million%2C%20according%20to%20an%20analysis%20of%20census%20data%20by%20the%20Harvard%20Joint%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Studies.%20Then%20came%20the%20pandemic%2C%20which%20cemented%20the%20idea%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-family-rentals-hit-road-bumps-after-years-growth-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esingle-family%20homes%20were%20a%20great%20bet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Booming%20housing%20demand%20drew%20all%20kinds%20of%20investors%20into%20the%20market%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202022%2C%20a%20Redfin%20analysis%20found%2C%20landlords%20accounted%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faverage-americans-beating-wall-street-new-homes-real-estate-homebuying-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2020%25%20of%20all%20home%20purchases%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstitutional%20investors%20%E2%80%94%20those%20with%20more%20than%201%2C000%20homes%20in%20their%20portfolios%20%E2%80%94%20own%20about%20426%2C000%20of%20the%2014.2%20million%20rental%20homes%20today%2C%20John%20Burns%20Research%20and%20Consulting%20found.%20Most%20of%20those%20properties%20are%20in%20sunny%20Southern%20places%20like%20Atlanta%20or%20Raleigh.%20Small-time%20landlords%20still%20dominate%20the%20single-family-rental%20landscape%2C%20but%20these%20aren't%20your%20mom%20and%20pop's%20%26quot%3Bmom-and-pops.%26quot%3B%20For%20one%2C%20the%20industry%20is%20vastly%20more%20transparent%20than%20it%20was%20in%20the%20early%202000s.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20see%20what%20comparable%20homes%20in%20your%20neighborhood%20are%20renting%20for%2C%20you%20can%20scroll%20through%20Zillow%20or%20visit%20the%20website%20of%20one%20of%20the%20institutional%20investors%2C%20such%20as%20Tricon%20Residential%2C%20Pretium%2C%20or%20Invitation%20Homes%2C%20all%20of%20which%20publicly%20list%20their%20properties%20and%20their%20asking%20rents.%20If%20even%20that%20sounds%20like%20too%20much%20work%2C%20companies%20including%20Buildium%20and%20Roofstock%2C%20known%20mostly%20for%20servicing%20the%20largest%20investors%20in%20the%20space%2C%20stand%20at%20the%20ready%20to%20offer%20property%20management%20and%20pricing%20advice%20%E2%80%94%20for%20a%20fee%2C%20of%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20all%20comes%20down%20to%20transparency%20and%20availability%20of%20information%2C%26quot%3B%20Rick%20Palacios%20Jr.%2C%20the%20director%20of%20research%20at%20John%20Burns%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20were%20to%20think%20about%20the%20single-family%20space%20today%20versus%2010%20years%20ago%2C%2015%20years%20ago%2C%20it's%20like%20night%20and%20day%2C%20just%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20availability%20of%20information%20that's%20out%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20everyone%20was%20scrambling%20for%20their%20piece%20of%20the%20suburbs%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20mom-and-pop%20landlords%20pounced%2C%20using%20these%20newfound%20tools%20to%20collect%20more%20cash.%20The%20median%20rent%20for%20single-family%20homes%20soared%20by%20double-digit%20percentages%20in%20both%202021%20and%202022%2C%20according%20to%20the%20property-data%20firm%20CoreLogic%2C%20peaking%20at%20a%20nearly%2014%25%20annual%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20there's%20this%20narrative%20that%20it's%20only%20institutional%20landlords%20or%20investors%20that%20push%20up%20rents%2C%20jack%20rents%2C%26quot%3B%20Palacios%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20absolutely%20not%20the%20case.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20on%20small%20landlords'%20behavior%20is%20notoriously%20scarce%2C%20but%20the%20latest%20John%20Burns%20figures%20show%20that%20in%20cities%20with%20little%20to%20no%20institutional%20presence%2C%20the%20smaller%20landlords%20are%20the%20ones%20cranking%20up%20the%20pressure.%20Chattanooga%2C%20Tennessee%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20has%20practically%20zero%20homes%20owned%20by%20institutional%20landlords%20but%20one%20of%20the%20country's%20highest%20rates%20of%20rent%20growth%20for%20single-family%20homes%2C%20with%20the%20typical%20asking%20rent%20for%20new%20leases%20up%2010%25%20in%20April%20from%20a%20year%20prior.%20Institutional%20investors%20own%20less%20than%201%25%20of%20single-family%20rentals%20in%20Grand%20Rapids%2C%20Michigan%2C%20but%20asking%20rents%20there%20were%20up%208%25%20year%20over%20year.%20In%20a%20similar%20vein%2C%20corporate%20owners%20may%20face%20the%20most%20scrutiny%20over%20evictions%2C%20but%20mom-and-pop%20rental%20owners%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20illegally%20evict%20their%20tenants%2C%20advocates%20for%20both%20landlords%20and%20tenants%20told%20Business%20Insider%20as%20part%20of%20a%20wide-ranging%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fillegal-wrongful-evictions-law-enforcement-police-court-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestigation%20into%20so-called%20%26quot%3Blockouts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMom-and-pop%20landlords%20may%20not%20be%20required%20to%20detail%20their%20operations%20in%20quarterly%20calls%20with%20stock%20analysts%2C%20but%20most%20experts%20I%20spoke%20with%20agreed%20that%20even%20those%20who%20own%20just%20a%20handful%20of%20properties%20are%20getting%20more%20with%20the%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMom-and-pop%20investors%20are%20very%20savvy%2C%20very%20much%20in%20tune%20with%20what's%20happening%2C%26quot%3B%20Jordan%20Kavana%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20chair%20of%20Ark%20Homes%20for%20Rent%2C%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20represent%20a%20huge%20opportunity%20for%20software%20companies%20and%20property-management%20firms%20to%20expand%20beyond%20their%20primary%20clients%20%E2%80%94%20deep-pocketed%20corporations%20%E2%80%94%20and%20target%20the%20vast%20number%20of%20smaller%20players.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20massive%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20Rich%20Ford%2C%20a%20cofounder%20of%20Vesta%20Ventures%2C%20a%20venture-capital%20firm%20with%20a%20heavy%20focus%20on%20the%20single-family-rental%20industry%2C%20told%20me.%20The%20firm%20has%20made%20investments%20in%20property-management-software%20companies%20like%20Hemlane%2C%20which%20offers%20%C3%A0%20la%20carte%20property-management%20services%20for%20small-time%20landlords%2C%20and%20Second%20Nature%2C%20which%20started%20out%20by%20delivering%20air%20filters%20to%20rental%20homes%20but%20now%20helps%20landlords%20offer%20%26quot%3Bresident%20benefit%20packages%26quot%3B%20that%20include%20things%20like%20renters%20insurance%2C%20move-in%20concierge%2C%20and%20avenues%20for%20tenants%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fdoes-rent-impact-credit-score%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuild%20credit%20through%20their%20rent%20payments%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStartups%20like%20Second%20Nature%20typically%20target%20the%20biggest%20players%20first%20%E2%80%94%20a%20single%20client%20can%20deploy%20the%20technology%20at%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20homes%20%E2%80%94%20but%20%26quot%3Bas%20you%20fine-tune%20your%20product%2C%20bring%20its%20cost%20down%2C%20etc.%2C%20now%20you've%20got%20the%20ability%20to%20spill%20into%20the%20mom-and-pop%20area%2C%26quot%3B%20Ford%20said.%20Hemlane%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20has%20always%20focused%20on%20smaller%20owners.%20The%20company%2C%20which%20estimates%20only%20one-fourth%20of%20single-family-rental%20landlords%20use%20professional%20management%20services%2C%20now%20manages%20more%20than%2028%2C000%20rentals%20on%20behalf%20of%20small%20landlords.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20groups%20are%20able%20to%20do%20things%20for%20those%20individual%20investors%2C%20landlords%2C%20in%20a%20way%20that%20%E2%80%94%20I%20think%20you%20could%20make%20a%20pretty%20strong%20case%20%E2%80%94%20kind%20of%20mirrors%20how%20institutions%20are%20managing%20their%20properties%2C%26quot%3B%20Palacios%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20day-to-day%20life%20of%20a%20landlord%20is%20filled%20with%20a%20million%20questions%3A%20Am%20I%20paying%20too%20much%20for%20insurance%3F%20Do%20I%20really%20need%20to%20shell%20out%20%3Cem%3Ethat%20%3C%2Fem%3Emuch%20for%20an%20electrical%20repair%3F%20In%20the%20past%2C%20small%20landlords%20might%20compare%20notes%2C%20but%20it%20was%20an%20inexact%20science.%20Now%20companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Froofstock-jll-technologies-stessa-single-family-rental-homes-real-estate-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStessa%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20offers%20a%20platform%20for%20landlords%20to%20manage%20everything%20from%20rent%20collection%20to%20bookkeeping%2C%20can%20gather%20all%20those%20data%20points%20from%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20investors%20and%20pass%20them%20down%20to%20the%20little%20guys.%20Individual%20landlords%20can%20look%20across%20their%20local%20markets%2C%20or%20even%20around%20the%20country%2C%20and%20understand%20how%20they%20stack%20up%20against%20their%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20something%20that%20institutions%20have%20been%20able%20to%20do%20for%20a%20long%20time%20because%20they%20have%20so%20many%20doors%2C%26quot%3B%20Devin%20Redmond%2C%20a%20marketing%20executive%20at%20Stessa%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20something%20that%20mom-and-pop%20landlords%20would%20go%20to%20their%20local%20meetup%20and%20they%20chat%20with%20people%2C%20and%20they%20might%20get%20five%20or%20six%20data%20points.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20will%20always%20be%20some%20landlords%20who%20seek%20nothing%20more%20than%20a%20tenant%20who%20pays%20rent%20on%20time%2C%20doesn't%20leave%2C%20and%20doesn't%20pick%20up%20the%20phone%20to%20complain%20when%20something%20breaks%20down.%20For%20this%20subset%2C%20the%20onslaught%20of%20proptech%20companies%20and%20landlord%20software%20may%20seem%20like%20unnecessary%20money%20sucks.%20But%20others%20will%20recognize%20the%20need%20to%20compete%20with%20the%20more%20professionalized%20newcomers%20%E2%80%94%20the%20landlords%2C%20both%20large%20and%20small%2C%20who%20fix%20things%20on%20time%2C%20let%20you%20pay%20online%2C%20and%2C%20yes%2C%20raise%20rents%20accordingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20growing%20adoption%20of%20these%20newfangled%20services%20raises%20a%20big%20question%3A%20What%20exactly%20does%20it%20mean%20to%20be%20a%20mom-and-pop%20landlord%20these%20days%3F%20The%20definition%20has%20never%20been%20scientific%20or%20even%20widely%20agreed%20upon.%20Instead%2C%20it%20conjures%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20folksy%2C%20almost%20romanticized%20affection%2C%26quot%3B%20Philip%20Garboden%2C%20who%20studies%20housing%20and%20property%20ownership%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%2C%20told%20me.%20It's%20been%20deployed%20in%20many%20contexts%3A%20You're%20just%20as%20likely%20to%20hear%20it%20in%20a%20CEO's%20quarterly%20recap%20as%20you%20are%20to%20hear%20it%20in%20a%20politician's%20stump%20speech.%20But%20the%20truth%20is%2C%20the%20term%20has%20outlived%20its%20usefulness.%20As%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freal-estate-smaller-landlords-faring-better-than-some-bigger-firms-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20ethos%20trickles%20down%20to%20small%20rental%20owners%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it'll%20be%20harder%20and%20harder%20to%20tell%20them%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVarious%20industry%20insiders%20I%20spoke%20with%20offered%20alternatives%20like%20%26quot%3Bsmall%20operator%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bretail%20investor%26quot%3B%20to%20describe%20the%20amateur%20landlord.%20None%20of%20these%20is%20nearly%20as%20evocative%20as%20%26quot%3Bmom-and-pop%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20maybe%20it%20doesn't%20matter.%20Rather%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-plan-cap-rent-5-percent-annually-corporate-landlords-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejudging%20landlords%20by%20their%20portfolio%20sizes%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20corporate%20structures%2C%20Garboden%20said%2C%20we%20should%20pay%20attention%20to%20their%20behaviors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20should%20really%20be%20concerned%20about%20management%20practices%2C%20fair%20housing%2C%20maintenance%2C%20all%20those%20types%20of%20things%2C%20and%20not%20be%20using%20these%20other%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20a%20landlord%20is%20large%20or%20small%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bas%20proxies%20for%20those%20behaviors%2C%26quot%3B%20Garboden%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20tools%20favored%20by%20big-time%20landlords%20may%20always%20be%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20smaller%20investors.%20Individuals%20may%20also%20be%20more%20hesitant%20to%20raise%20rents%20in%20line%20with%20institutional%20players%20since%20a%20vacancy%20for%20a%20month%20or%20two%20is%20much%20more%20costly%20when%20you%20have%20a%20couple%20houses%20than%20when%20you%20have%2010%2C000.%20But%20the%20gap%20is%20narrowing%20as%20small%20rental%20owners%20capitalize%20on%20the%20innovations%20that%20the%20institutional%20class%20has%20already%20embraced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaniel%2C%20the%20landlord%20in%20Atlanta%2C%20told%20me%20he%20now%20coaches%20his%20friends%20on%20how%20to%20maximize%20their%20cash%20flow%20from%20investment%20properties.%20His%20arrangement%20with%20Roofstock%2C%20the%20company%20that%20manages%20his%20properties%2C%20frees%20him%20up%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20sourcing%20deals.%20Even%20when%20he%20owned%20only%20one%20home%2C%20he%20told%20me%