2%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fvicky-kaushal-reveals-he-is-the-most-rational-guy-in-room-appreciates-katrina-kaifs-emotional-intelligence%2Farticleshow%2F111800867.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20Food%20In%20Space%20Falls%20Flat%20-%20The%20Surprising%20Connection%20To%20Gravity%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAstronauts%20often%20report%20that%20the%20joy%20of%20eating%20is%20lost%20in%20space.%20Food%20that%20tastes%20fabulous%20on%20Earth%20may%20become%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0899900702009358%3Fvia%253Dihub%5C%22%3Ebland%20and%20boring%20in%20orbit%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20despite%20carefully%20designed%20diets%2C%20space%20travellers%20often%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2Fhuman-adaptation-2021-final.pdf%5C%22%3Estruggle%20to%20eat%20enough%20to%20meet%20their%20energy%20needs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat's%20going%20on%20here%3F%20We%20carried%20out%20some%20experiments%20on%20Earth%20to%20find%20out%2C%20using%20virtual%20reality%20(VR)%20and%20a%20simulated%20spacecraft%20environment%20to%20study%20how%20space%20travel%20might%20affect%20a%20person's%20sense%20of%20smell%20and%20experience%20of%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20discovered%20that%20some%20smells%20seem%20much%20more%20intense%20in%20a%20space-like%20environment%20%E2%80%93%20and%20earlier%20theories%20about%20how%20zero%20gravity%20affects%20the%20body%20can't%20be%20the%20whole%20story.%20Our%20results%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fifst.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1111%2Fijfs.17306%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20International%20Journal%20of%20Food%20Science%20and%20Technology%2C%20could%20help%20design%20the%20space%20menus%20of%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EEating%20is%20a%20complicated%20experience%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEating%20is%20a%20multi-sensory%20experience%20that%20involves%20sight%2C%20smell%2C%20taste%2C%20hearing%2C%20and%20touch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20enjoy%20the%20flavour%20of%20food%20%E2%80%93%20say%2C%20when%20biting%20into%20an%20apple%20%E2%80%93%20we%20need%20a%20combination%20of%20sensations%2C%20including%20taste%20(sweet%2C%20sour)%2C%20smell%20(the%20complex%20combination%20of%20apple%20aromas)%2C%20texture%20(the%20crunch)%2C%20colour%20(green%2C%20red)%2C%20and%20touch%20(firmness).%20If%20any%20of%20these%20senses%20is%20dulled%2C%20our%20enjoyment%20of%20food%20will%20not%20be%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20experience%20of%20food%20in%20space%20is%20very%20different%20from%20what%20we%20are%20used%20to%20on%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20possible%20explanation%20for%20why%20space%20travellers%20experience%20taste%20differently%20involves%20the%20lack%20of%20gravity.%20Without%20gravity%2C%20bodily%20fluids%20are%20not%20drawn%20towards%20the%20feet%20but%20instead%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fift.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1111%2Fj.1365-2621.2002.tb10622.x%5C%22%3Eshift%20towards%20the%20head%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20sensation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fift.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1111%2F1541-4337.12633%5C%22%3Elike%20having%20a%20blocked%20nose%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20you've%20ever%20had%20a%20cold%2C%20you%20know%20how%20difficult%20it%20is%20to%20taste%20and%20enjoy%20food%20without%20your%20sense%20of%20smell.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20could%20there%20be%20other%20reasons%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EThe%20importance%20of%20environment%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20space%2C%20the%20environment%20is%20unfamiliar%20and%20consistently%20monotonous.%20Could%20this%20change%20our%20perception%20of%20food%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EContext%20heavily%20contributes%20to%20the%20eating%20experience.%20Studies%20have%20shown%20that%20eating%20the%20same%20meal%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.infona.pl%2Fresource%2Fbwmeta1.element.elsevier-82188b09-5e0d-341c-a5c2-826baefddca6%5C%22%3Edifferent%20settings%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20lead%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0950329302001891%5C%22%3Evarying%20opinions%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20meal.%20Think%20about%20enjoying%20a%20picnic%20sandwich%20in%20a%20scenic%20park%20versus%20eating%20the%20same%20sandwich%20quickly%20at%20your%20work%20desk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20spacecraft%20is%20an%20enclosed%20and%20confined%20environment%2C%20an%20airtight%20container%20in%20which%20you%20are%20surrounded%20by%20wiring%20and%20equipment%20and%20with%20no%20boundary%20between%20work%20and%20personal%20space.%20Imagine%20being%20in%20a%20pandemic-grade%20lockdown%20for%20multiple%20years%20with%20limited%20food%20and%20essential%20goods%20(and%20a%20persistent%20blocked%20nose).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1111%2Fjoss.12254%5C%22%3Etaste-test%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20compared%20airline%20meals%20consumed%20in%20three%20settings%3A%20a%20classic%20sensory%20laboratory%20environment%20(quiet%2C%20closed%20or%20semi-closed%20cubicles%20%E2%80%93%20like%20a%20voting%20booth)%2C%20a%20semi-realistic%20aircraft%20environment%20simulated%20in%20a%20laboratory%20using%20aircraft%20furnishings%2C%20and%20an%20actual%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPassengers%20in%20the%20simulated%20aircraft%20environment%20enjoyed%20their%20meals%20about%20as%20much%20as%20passengers%20on%20an%20actual%20flight%20did.%20(Both%20of%20them%20liked%20it%20less%20than%20the%20people%20in%20the%20lab%20environment%20did.)%20This%20suggests%20the%20aircraft%20environment%20has%20a%20significant%20influence%20on%20food%20enjoyment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EBringing%20space%20to%20Earth%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearch%20involving%20humans%20in%20space%20is%20very%20challenging.%20Space%20missions%20typically%20involve%20at%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Finternational-space-station%2Fspace-station-facts-and-figures%2F%5C%22%3Esix%20or%20seven%20crew%20members%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20limits%20the%20sample%20size%20for%20experiments%20and%20the%20predictive%20power%20of%20the%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20for%20food%20research%2C%20each%20person%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS221479931500048X%5C%22%3Eunique%20sensory%20experiences%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20responses%20toward%20them.%20This%20makes%20it%20challenging%20to%20understand%20how%20different%20individuals%20perceive%20smells%20in%20space%2C%20let%20alone%20food%20aromas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20set%20out%20to%20recreate%20space%20on%20Earth.%20Using%20VR%2C%20we%20simulated%20the%20environment%20of%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20VR%20setup%20let%20us%20obtain%20data%20about%20participants'%20feelings%20regarding%20food%20stimuli%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20moment%E2%80%9D%2C%20rather%20than%20waiting%20for%20them%20to%20take%20off%20the%20headset%20and%20asking%20them%20questions%20afterwards.%20VR%20is%20a%20vital%20training%20environment%20for%20astronauts%20because%20of%20its%20unmatched%20ability%20to%20create%20a%20realistic%20sense%20of%20presence%2C%20crucial%20for%20studying%20what%20it%20is%20like%20to%20live%20in%20a%20spacecraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F607409%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240717-17-6ja26d.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D1000%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20of%20a%20person%20wearing%20a%20VR%20headset%20and%20sniffing%20a%20small%20container%20held%20under%20their%20nose.%5C%22%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%20600px)%20600px%2C%20237px%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F607409%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240717-17-6ja26d.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D450%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F607409%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240717-17-6ja26d.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D450%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F607409%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240717-17-6ja26d.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D450%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%201800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F607409%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240717-17-6ja26d.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D566%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20754w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F607409%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240717-17-6ja26d.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D566%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201508w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F607409%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240717-17-6ja26d.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D566%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%202262w%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F607409%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240717-17-6ja26d.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-4.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D754%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%5Cn%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cspan%3EParticipants%20smelled%20different%20scents%20while%20immersed%20in%20a%20VR%20space%20station%20environment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESeamus%20Daniel%20%2F%20RMIT%20University%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20study%20is%20the%20first%20to%20involve%20a%20significant%20sample%20size%20(54%20people)%20to%20capture%20the%20variation%20of%20individuals'%20personal%20experiences%20of%20aromas%20and%20taste%20in%20simulated%20isolated%20settings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20study%20comparing%20everyday%20aromas%2C%20some%20scents%20were%20perceived%20differently%20in%20the%20virtual%20International%20Space%20Station%20environment%20compared%20to%20the%20partitioned%20booth%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EMolecular%20magic%20of%20aroma%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAromas%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontiersin.org%2Fjournals%2Fchemistry%2Farticles%2F10.3389%2Ffchem.2022.820749%2Ffull%5C%22%3Ea%20complex%20blend%20of%20molecules%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20unique%20chemical%20structures%2C%20influencing%20how%20they%20interact%20with%20the%20olfactory%20receptors%20in%20the%20nose%20to%20form%20distinctive%20smells.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOur%20study%20suggests%20that%20only%20specific%20aroma%20compounds%20are%20perceived%20differently%20in%20space-like%20environments.%20We%20found%20that%20sweet-smelling%20molecules%20tended%20to%20be%20perceived%20more%20strongly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVanilla%20and%20almond%2C%20which%20both%20contain%20the%20sweet%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubs.acs.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1021%2Facs.jafc.8b05845%5C%22%3Ealmond-%20or%20cherry-scented%3C%2Fa%3E%20compound%20benzaldehyde%2C%20smelled%20stronger%20in%20our%20VR%20space%20station%20than%20in%20the%20control%20environment.%20By%20contrast%2C%20there%20was%20no%20difference%20in%20perception%20of%20the%20lemon%20aroma.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20knowledge%20could%20be%20used%20in%20designing%20space%20meals.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20sweet%20aromas%20could%20be%20used%20as%20flavour%20enhancers%20or%20additives%20to%20bring%20out%20other%20flavours%20and%20add%20depth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20how%20these%20aroma%20compounds%20interact%20with%20each%20other%2C%20and%20finding%20the%20right%20concentration%20levels%20is%20essential.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20no%20single%20flavour%20will%20suit%20everybody's%20taste.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EEarthly%20implications%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20better%20understanding%20of%20how%20smell%20is%20perceived%20in%20space-like%20environments%20could%20inspire%20ways%20to%20create%20personalised%20diets%20based%20on%20each%20astronaut's%20unique%20sensory%20experiences%20and%20preferences.%20By%20tailoring%20food%20aromas%2C%20we%20could%20encourage%20space%20travellers%20not%20only%20to%20eat%20more%2C%20but%20enjoy%20food%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20solutions%20may%20also%20help%20people%20on%20Earth%20living%20in%20isolated%20or%20confined%20environments%2C%20such%20as%20nursing%20home%20residents%2C%20individuals%20on%20military%20deployment%2C%20and%20submarine%20crews.%3Cimg%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F234468%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E(%3Cstrong%3EAuthors%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fjulia-low-1539939%5C%22%3EJulia%20Low%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Senior%20Lecturer%20in%20Nutrition%20and%20Food%20(Sensory%20Science)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Frmit-university-1063%5C%22%3ERMIT%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fgrace-loke-mei-ing-1543860%5C%22%3EGrace%20Loke%20Mei%20Ing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20PhD%20Candidate%20in%20Food%20Science%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Frmit-university-1063%5C%22%3ERMIT%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fian-peake-1548471%5C%22%3EIan%20Peake%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Digital%20Solutions%20Architect%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Frmit-university-1063%5C%22%3ERMIT%2