ion%20Of%20Signals%20Led%20To%20Bengal%20Train%20Accident%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20accident%20involving%20Kanchanjunga%20Express%20and%20a%20goods%20train%20in%20West%20Bengal's%20Darjeeling%20district%20last%20month%20occurred%20due%20to%20wrong%20interpretation%20of%20signals%20by%20the%20goods%20train%20driver%2C%20according%20to%20a%20preliminary%20report%20accessed%20by%20NDTV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20%26quot%3Blapses%20at%20multiple%20levels%20in%20managing%20the%20train%20operations%20under%20Automatic%20Signal%20Failures%26quot%3B%2C%20which%20led%20to%20the%20collision%2C%20said%20the%20report%20submitted%20by%20the%20Commissioner%20of%20Railway%20Safety%20(CRS).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20gave%20a%20clean%20chit%20to%20the%20express%20train's%20loco%20pilot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%2010%20people%20died%20and%20dozens%20others%20were%20injured%20as%20the%20Kanchanjunga%20Express%20was%20hit%20by%20a%20goods%20train%20near%20New%20Jalpaiguri%20on%20June%2017.%20The%20express%20train%20was%20travelling%20from%20Agartala%20in%20Tripura%20to%20Sealdah%20in%20Kolkata.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20loco%20pilot%20of%20the%20goods%20train%20and%20two%20other%20railway%20staff%20were%20among%20the%20dead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%2C%20which%20classified%20the%20accident%20in%20%26quot%3BError%20in%20Train%20Working%26quot%3B%20category%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20a%20wrong%20paper%20authority%20was%20issued%20to%20cross%20an%20area%20where%20automatic%20signalling%20system%20is%20not%20functional.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20error%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report%2C%20was%20that%20the%20loco%20pilot%20was%20not%20alerted%20to%20maintain%20a%20particular%20speed-limit%20while%20crossing%20the%20area%20with%20no%20automatic%20signalling%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20found%20that%20the%20loco%20pilot%20and%20the%20train%20manager%20were%20not%20provided%20with%20walkie%20talkies%2C%20which%20co