0more%20farmers%20make%20the%20switch.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Sowmya%20Mani%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Farmer%20Earns%205%20Times%20More%20with%20Hydroponics%20%26amp%3B%20Saves%2080%25%20on%20Electricity%20Bills%3B%20Helps%20Others%20Switch%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EUntil%202016%2C%20Pritpal%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20family%20in%20Chandigarh%20had%20been%20cultivating%20wheat%20and%20paddy%20for%2050%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20culture%20of%20monocropping%20is%20prevalent%20in%20Punjab%20and%20Haryana%20where%20most%20families%20grow%20paddy%20and%20wheat%20throughout%20both%20Kharif%20and%20Rabi%20seasons.%20Sticking%20to%20specific%20crops%20year%20after%20year%20eventually%20leads%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20soil-borne%20diseases%20and%20substantially%20decreases%20the%20fertility%20of%20soil%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPritpal%20was%20always%20intrigued%20by%20new%20ways%20to%20make%20farming%20more%20profitable%20and%20reduce%20the%20risks%20associated%20with%20traditional%20agricultural%20practices.%20This%20quest%20led%20him%20to%20quit%20his%20three-year%20long%20corporate%20career%20and%20turn%20to%20farming.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CComing%20from%20a%20family%20of%20farmers%2C%20I%20was%20always%20connected%20to%20my%20roots%2C%20even%20during%20my%20higher%20studies%20in%20Nagpur%20and%20my%20job%20in%20Mumbai.%20Whenever%20I%20got%20a%20chance%2C%20I%20visited%20my%20farm%2C%20contemplating%20how%20to%20transform%20it%20into%20a%20profitable%20venture%20for%20the%20next%20generation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20told%20my%20parents%20about%20my%20decision%20to%20pursue%20farming%20full-time%2C%20their%20first%20concern%20was%20also%20about%20the%20new%20approaches%20I%20wanted%20to%20try%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20the%20MBA%20graduate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPritpal%20went%20on%20to%20turn%20his%20ancestral%20farm%20into%20a%20thriving%20business%20with%2025%2C000%20green%20leafy%20plants%20such%20as%20lettuce%20and%20spinach%20flourishing%20in%20an%208%2C000%20square-feet%20area.%20Every%20month%2C%20he%20harvests%20up%20to%20800%20kg%20of%20leafy%20greens%2C%20achieving%20five%20times%20the%20yield%20compared%20to%20conventional%20farming%20while%20using%20fewer%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20possible%20due%20to%20the%20protected%20cultivation%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F336600%2Ftech-nursery-hydroponics-aeroponics-farming-ratlam-brothers-arbind-ravindra-dhakad%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esystem%20of%20hydroponics%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewhere%20crops%20are%20grown%20without%20soil!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20many%20soil%20borne%20diseases%20such%20as%20fungal%20and%20bacterial%20infections%20that%20affect%20crop%20yield.%20You%20cannot%20eliminate%20microorganisms%20and%20parasites%20like%20nematodes%20from%20the%20soil.%20So%2C%20I%20thought%20of%20eliminating%20soil%20itself%20as%20a%20medium%20altogether.%20I%20turned%20to%20hydroponics%2C%20which%20eliminates%20this%20worry%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPritpal%20now%20grows%20exotic%20leafy%20greens%20such%20as%20Italian%20basil%2C%20baby%20spinach%2C%20three%20to%20four%20kinds%20of%20lettuces%2C%20vine%20crops%20like%20red%20and%20yellow%20capsicum%20and%20seedless%20cucumbers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20grows%20these%20crops%20in%202.5%20acres%20of%20land%20comprising%20multiple%20types%20of%20protected%20environment%20structures%2C%20including%20an%20indoor%20vertical%20farm%2C%20a%20temperature-controlled%20polyhouse%2C%20a%20naturally-ventilated%20polyhouse%2C%20and%20indoor%20and%20outdoor%20hydroponics%20setups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2FPritpal-4-1721052314.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pritpal%20grows%20leafy%20greens%20like%20lettuce%20and%20vegetables%20like%20capsicum.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2FPritpal-4-1721052314.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2FPritpal-4-1721052314-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2FPritpal-4-1721052314-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2FPritpal-4-1721052314-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2FPritpal-4-1721052314-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-356985%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EPritpal%20grows%20leafy%20greens%20like%20lettuce%20and%20vegetables%20like%20capsicum.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20sat%20down%20with%20Pritpal%20to%20understand%20his%20switch%20from%20traditional%20open%20field%20cultivation%20to%20protected%20farming%20techniques.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EGrowing%20crops%20the%20new%20way%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20researching%2C%20Pritpal%20came%20to%20know%20about%20protected%20cultivation%20and%20greenhouse%20farming.%20In%202016%2C%20he%20started%20cultivating%20exotic%20flowers%20and%20vegetables%20like%20seedless%20cucumbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%2C%20he%20was%20also%20introduced%20to%20the%20hydroponics%20method%20of%20cultivation.%20Talking%20about%20its%20advantages%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CHydroponics%20allows%20us%20to%20grow%20leafy%20greens%20locally%20in%20a%20temperature-controlled%20environment%20all%20year%20round.%20It%20gives%20you%20more%20control%20over%20the%20growing%20part.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20goes%20on%20to%20explain%20how%20this%20method%20also%20saves%2090%20percent%20water%20compared%20to%20open-field%20farming%20as%20it%20keeps%20circulating%20it%20within%20the%20setup.%20This%20makes%20the%20whole%20technique%20a%20sustainable%20way%20of%20growing%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20also%20reduces%20nutrient%20costs%2C%20as%20we%20only%20add%20the%20precise%20amount%20needed%20for%20plant%20growth%2C%20unlike%20in%20open-field%20farming%20where%20large%20quantities%20of%20fertilisers%20are%20used%20without%20control%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPritpal%20says%20that%20he%20invested%20Rs%2060%20lakh%20in%20setting%20up%20the%20whole%20system%20on%20a%202.5%20acre%20farm.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20this%20is%20only%20a%20one-time%20investment%2C%20yielding%20recurring%20benefits%20throughout%20the%20year%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20he%20grows%20leafy%20greens%20hydroponically%20and%20harvests%20up%20to%20800%20kg%20of%20produce%20every%20month.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20leafy%20greens%2C%20the%20yield%20is%20almost%20five%20times%20greater%20compared%20to%20traditional%20land-based%20farming.%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20beauty%20of%20hydroponics%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPritpal%20also%20grows%20bell%20peppers%20and%20seedless%20cucumbers%20in%20a%20naturally-ventilated%20polyhouse%20spanning%20across%201.5%20acres.%20Annually%2C%20he%20harvests%20up%20to%2090%20tonnes%20of%20seedless%20cucumbers%20and%20up%20to%2030%20tonnes%20of%20bell%20peppers.%20%E2%80%9CI%20get%20a%2030%20percent%20higher%20return%20in%20this%20setup%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2FPritpal-5-1721052345.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%