ing%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98I%20still%20see%20hope%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Ghosh%20returned%20home%2C%20he%20realised%20that%20his%20village%20and%20the%20nearby%20villages%20still%20did%20not%20have%20any%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CChildren%20were%20travelling%20to%20different%20villages%20to%20study%2C%20and%20the%20dropout%20rate%20was%20quite%20high.%20Most%20students%20were%20economically%20disadvantaged%20with%20no%20options%20for%20a%20better%20education.%20These%20children%20not%20only%20came%20from%20poor%20homes%20but%20also%20belonged%20to%20scheduled%20castes%2C%20facing%20a%20lot%20of%20casteism%20and%20unfair%20discrimination%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhosh%20decided%20that%20he%20needed%20to%20do%20something.%20%E2%80%9CI%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20Government%20and%20raised%20the%20matter.%20I%20did%20all%20the%20research%20and%20then%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20State%20Government%20with%20the%20request%20of%20opening%20a%20junior%20high%20school%20in%20the%20village%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Ghosh%20secured%20the%20approvals%20in%202010%2C%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20school%20did%20not%20start%20until%202014.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20know%20how%20government%20work%20is%20%E2%80%94%20slow%20as%20a%20snail.%20I%20dedicated%20all%20my%20time%20to%20getting%20the%20construction%20process%20started.%20The%20ruling%20party%20leaders%20at%20the%20time%20did%20not%20support%20me%20at%20all%2C%20but%20I%20had%20strong%20faith%20that%20everything%20would%20work%20out.%20Eventually%2C%20when%20the%20construction%20did%20start%2C%20it%20was%20the%20poor%20people%20of%20the%20village%20who%20helped%20me%20complete%20it%20quickly%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhosh%20faced%20another%20challenge%20when%20the%20school%20needed%20permanent%20teachers%20appointed.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20been%20struggling%20with%20no%20permanent%20teachers%20for%20years.%20Back%20then%2C%20I%20was%20faced